<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        body{
            background-color: aquamarine;
        }
        #heading{
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 id = 'heading'>Title</h1>
    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>Create a basic HTML page to demonstrate your understanding of the DOM and its structure. Your task is to write JavaScript that performs the following actions:</p>
    <div class="container">
        <ol>
            <li>Select the element by its id and change its text content to "Welcome to the DOM World!".</li>
            <li>Select all elements using getElementsByTagName and set their text color to blue.</li>
            <li>Use querySelector to select the first with the class container and change its background color to yellow.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>Submission</h3>
        <p>Submit your Masai GitHub repository link containing the HTML and JavaScript files.</p>
    </div>    
</body>
</html>
<script>
    let heading = document.getElementById('heading')
    heading.textContent='Understanding and Navigating the DOM'

    let para = document.getElementsByTagName('p')
    for(let i =0; i<para.length; i++){
        para[i].style.color = 'blue'
    }

    let div = document.querySelector('.container')
    div.style.background = 'yellow'
</script>
